8001 def checksum(value: str) -> str:
8002 """
8003 Calculates the checksum char used for the 16th char.
8004 Author: Vincenzo Palazzo
8005 """
8006 return chr(65 + sum(CHECKSUM_TABLE[index % 2][ALPHANUMERICS_DICT[char]] for index, char in enumerate(value)) % 26)
8007  
8008  
8009 class Provider(SsnProvider):
8010 """
8011 Generates italian fiscal codes.
8012 """
8013  
8014 def ssn(self) -> str:
8015 sex: int = self.random_int(min=0, max=1)
8016 surname: str = self._get_surname_letters()
8017 name: str = self._get_name_letters(sex)
8018 year: str = "%02d" % self.random_int(min=0, max=99)
8019 month: str = self.random_element(MONTHS_LIST)
8020 day: str = "%02d" % (self.random_int(min=1, max=28) + (40 if sex == 1 else 0))
8021 municipality: str = self.random_element(MUNICIPALITIES_LIST)
8022 code: str = f"{surname}{name}{year}{month}{day}{municipality}"
8023 return code + checksum(code)
8024  
8025 vat_id_formats = ("IT###########",)
8026  
8027 def vat_id(self) -> str:
8028 """
8029 http://ec.europa.eu/taxation_customs/vies/faq.html#item_11
8030 :return: A random Italian VAT ID
8031 """
8032 return self.bothify(self.random_element(self.vat_id_formats))
8033  
8034 def _get_name_letters(self, sex: int) -> str:
8035 """
8036 Rules:
8037 * take all consonants in their order
8038 * if >= 4, take the 1st, 3rd and 4th
8039 * if < 3 take the vowels also; vowels must go _after_ the consonants
8040 and must be taken in the order they appear (LUCA -> LCU)
8041 * if == 3 return all 3 consonants
8042 * if name is < 3 chars, pad it on the right with "X" (LI -> LIX)
8043 Args:
8044 sex: int
8045 Returns:
8046 str
8047 """
8048  
8049 if sex == 1:
8050 name = self.generator.first_name_male().upper()
8051 else:
8052 name = self.generator.first_name_female().upper()
8053  
8054 if len(name) < 3:
8055 return self._pad_shorter(name)
8056  
8057 name_consonants = self._get_consonants(name)
8058 cons_len = len(name_consonants)
8059 if cons_len >= 4:
8060 name_part = "".join([name_consonants[0], name_consonants[1], name_consonants[3]])
8061 elif cons_len < 3:
8062 name_part = "".join(name_consonants + self._get_vowels(name))[:3]
8063 else:
8064 name_part = "".join(name_consonants)
8065 return name_part
8066  
8067 def _get_surname_letters(self) -> str:
8068 """
8069 Rules:
8070 * if consonants >=3 : take the first 3
  • E501 Line too long (120 > 119 characters)
8071 * if less, pad them with vowels; vowels come after the consonants and in the order they appear (ROSA -> RSO)
8072 * if surname is less than 3 chars, pad it on the right with 'X' (FO -> FOX)
8073 Returns:
8074 str
8075 """
8076 surname = self.generator.last_name().upper()
8077 if len(surname) < 3:
8078 return self._pad_shorter(surname)
8079  
8080 surname_consonants = self._get_consonants(surname)
8081 cons_len = len(surname_consonants)
8082  
8083 if cons_len < 3:
8084 surname_part = "".join(surname_consonants + self._get_vowels(surname))[:3]
8085 else:
8086 surname_part = "".join(surname_consonants)[:3]
8087 return surname_part
8088  
8089 @staticmethod
8090 def _get_vowels(sequence: str) -> list:
8091 """
8092 Returns list of vowels in provided string
8093 """
8094 vowels = []
8095 for char in sequence:
8096 if char in VOWELS:
8097 vowels.append(char)
8098 return vowels
8099  
8100 @staticmethod
8101 def _get_consonants(sequence: str) -> list:
8102 """
8103 Returns list of consonants in provided string
8104 """
8105 consonants = []
8106 for char in sequence:
8107 if char in CONSONANTS:
8108 consonants.append(char)
8109 return consonants
8110  
8111 @staticmethod
